## Binary:
13 = 1101
      ↑
    bit 2
(Bit positions start from 0 on the right)
3 2 1 0
1 1 0 1

Create a mask with only the i-th bit set.
1 << i

For i = 2:
0001 << 2   (1*2^2 = 4)
0100

Now AND it with n.
1101
0100
----
0100
Result is non-zero.
Therefore bit is set.

CODE-->
class Solution {
public:
    bool checkIthBit(int n, int i) {
       
       if(n & (1<<i))
       return true;
    }
};
